  "body": "https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/91cb6f863a965481e51d5d9c0e5ccd54796fd967/core/types/transaction.go#L151-L160\r\n\r\nFirst byte in range `[0, 0x7f]` are 2718 transactions, but not every first byte in the range `[0x80, 0xff]` is a legacy transaction.  While I suspect that `rlp.DecodeBytes` will correctly error on any invalid legacy transaction today, there is a very marginal risk that some future change could result in transactions with a leading byte outside of the `[0xc0, 0xfe]` not failing the `rlp.DecodeBytes` function at which point a consensus bug could occur.\r\n\r\nAt the least, the comment should probably be updated to make it clear that not all transactions in the `[0x80, 0xff]` range are legacy transactions.\r\n\r\nNote: I recognize this is *incredibly* minor and arguably nitpicky, so I won't be offended if it gets closed without being fixed.",
