    "body": "Myeah, this is too nitpicky. The id range for new txs were explicitly chosen not to overlap with the RLP encoding. It is a very deliberate decision so I don't think it will just be forgotten. RLP itself is kind of \"done\", with no changes ever being made to make parsing more relaxed. And we want to switch everything over to SSZ soon, so RLP itself for txs will die out pretty fast.\r\n\r\nTL;DR: There's not much point to tweak code that works and has a limited shelf life at this point :) But thanks for the notice!",
